<subSubSection id="C31665703239FFD383E9FA982FEAF9B2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336FB3239FFD383E9FA982FEAF9B2" blockId="6.[151,1437,1375,1654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD3826AFA982DB5FABE" authorityName="Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss" authorityYear="2006" box="[276,414,1375,1401]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD3826AFA982DB5FABE" box="[276,414,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Cerradomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises eight species, namely: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD3805FFAA72916FABE" authority="(Bonvicino, Casado &amp; Weksler 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Bonvicino, Casado &amp; Weksler" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[801,1341,1375,1402]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="akroai">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD3805FFAA72FA1FABE" box="[801,906,1375,1402]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. akroai</emphasis>
(Bonvicino, Casado &amp; Weksler 2014)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD38637FAA72E5DFA5A" authority="(Tavares, Pessoa &amp; Goncalves 2011)" baseAuthorityName="Tavares, Pessoa &amp; Goncalves" baseAuthorityYear="2011" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goytaca">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD38637FAA72CECFA5A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. goytaca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3239FFD383A6FA442E44FA5A" author="Tavares, W. C. &amp; Pessoa, L. M. &amp; Goncalves, P. R." box="[216,623,1411,1437]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="645 - 658" refId="ref74464" refString="Tavares, W. C., Pessoa, L. M. &amp; Goncalves, P. R. (2011) New species of Cerradomys from coastal sandy plains of southeastern Brazil (Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae). Journal of Mammalogy, 92 (3), 645 - 658. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 10 - MAMM- 096.1" type="journal article" year="2011">Tavares, Pêssoa &amp; Gonçalves 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD381FAFA43296AFA5A" authority="(Percequillo, Hingst-Zaher &amp; Bonvincino 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Percequillo, Hingst-Zaher &amp; Bonvincino" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[644,1345,1411,1438]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="langguthi">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD381FAFA432F39FA5A" box="[644,786,1411,1438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. langguthi</emphasis>
(Percequillo, Hingst-Zaher &amp; Bonvincino 2008)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD38630FA432EA6FA06" authority="(Langguth &amp; Bonvincino 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Langguth &amp; Bonvincino" baseAuthorityYear="2002" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maracajuensis">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD38630FA432D33FA06" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. maracajuensis</emphasis>
(Langguth &amp; Bonvincino 2002)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD381E4FA6F2823FA06" authority="(Bonvincino 2003)" baseAuthorityName="Bonvincino" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[666,1032,1447,1474]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marinhus">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD381E4FA6F2F0CFA06" box="[666,807,1447,1474]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. marinhus</emphasis>
(Bonvincino 2003)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD3876BFA6F2CF0FA22" authority="(Langguth &amp; Bonvincino 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Langguth &amp; Bonvincino" baseAuthorityYear="2002" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scotti">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD3876BFA6F285EFA06" box="[1045,1141,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. scotti</emphasis>
(Langguth &amp; Bonvincino 2002)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD38397FA0B2E00FA22" authority="(Wagner 1842)" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[233,555,1483,1510]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subflavus">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD38397FA0B2D5EFA22" box="[233,373,1483,1510]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. subflavus</emphasis>
(Wagner 1842)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783239FFD38114FA0B28D8FA22" authority="(Percequillo, Hingst-Zaher &amp; Bonvincino 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Percequillo, Hingst-Zaher &amp; Bonvincino" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[618,1267,1483,1510]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vivoi">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD38114FA0B2EE8FA22" box="[618,707,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. vivoi</emphasis>
(Percequillo, Hingst-Zaher &amp; Bonvincino 2008)
</taxonomicName>
. These species occur in the open vegetation belt that crosses South America from north-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F31B766B3239FFD38743FA2828AAF9CE" box="[1085,1153,1519,1545]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
to south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F31B766B3239FFD38634FA2829B7F9CE" box="[1354,1436,1519,1545]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and north-western 
<collectingCountry id="F31B766B3239FFD38212F9D32DFFF9E9" box="[364,468,1556,1582]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3239FFD3829AF9D42EECF9EA" author="Weksler, M. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Voss, R. S." box="[484,711,1555,1582]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref76039" refString="Weksler, M., Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Voss, R. S. (2006) Ten new genera of oryzomyine rodents (Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 3537, 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="2006">
Weksler 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD38137F9D32E57F9EA" box="[585,636,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3239FFD381ADF9D42FF3F9EA" author="Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Hingst-Zaher, E. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." box="[723,984,1555,1582]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 46" refId="ref71570" refString="Percequillo, A. R., Hingst-Zaher, E. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2008) Systematic review of genus Cerradomys Weksler, Percequillo and Voss, 2006 (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini), with description of two new species from eastern Brazil. American Museum Novitates, 3622, 1 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 495.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Percequillo 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93239FFD38025F9D32FA5F9EA" box="[859,910,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3239FFD3809BF9D4293BF9EA" author="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R." box="[997,1296,1555,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref72147" refString="Prado, J. R. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. (2013) Geographic distribution of the genera of the tribe Oryzomyini (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae) in South America: patterns of distribution and diversity. Archivos de Zoologia, 44 (1), 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2176 - 7793. v 44 i 1 p 1 - 120" type="journal article" year="2013">Prado &amp; Percequillo 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3239FFD38663F9D42CC9F995" author="Percequillo, A. R." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="300 - 308" refId="ref71228" refString="Percequillo, A. R. (2015 b) Genus Cerradomys Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss, 2006. In: Patton, J., Pardinas, U. F. J. &amp; D'Elia, G. (Eds.), Mammals of South America. 2. Rodents. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, Illinois, pp. 300 - 308." type="book chapter" year="2015">Percequillo 2015b</bibRefCitation>
). All cytogenetic data available for the genus was presented on 
<tableCitation id="C68E03403239FFD380CBF9F02820F996" box="[949,1035,1591,1617]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,235,587,612]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="TABLE 2. Karyotype data of genus Cerradomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Table 2</tableCitation>
, and the distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens were presented on 
<figureCitation id="13372A7E3239FFD38006F99C2F96F9B2" box="[888,957,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,281,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-69@7.[151,1436,273,1168]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Cerradomys. (□) C. akroai; (■) C. goytaca; (ê) C. langguthi; (r) C. maracajuensis; (▲) C. marinhus; (○) C. scotti; (☆) C. subflavus; (l) C. vivoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423619/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
